f{% render 'section-new-faq-jewelry-styles-min' %}
<div class="section-container">
                <h2 class="faq-title hero__overlay-title section-title has-animated">
                    Fine Jewelry FAQs
                </h2>
            <div class="new-faq_wrapp">
                <div class="new-faq_item">
                    <div class="new-faq_item-title">
                        <p class="font-title">
                            How do you authenticate jewelry?
                        </p>
                        <a href="javascript:void(0)"  class="font-title">
                            +
                        </a>
                    </div>
                    <div class="new-faq_item-text">
                        <p class="font-description">
                          Authenticating a piece of fine jewelry is a hard and meticulous process that involves a lot of experience within the field. 
<br><br>
Professionals consider several factors, including the brand, craftsmanship, materials used, and hallmarks. They closely examine the gemstone quality, assessing their cut, metal type, clarity, color, and carat weight. 
<br><br>
Hallmarks, such as stamps indicating metal purity, manufacturer, and country of origin, are also scrutinized. 
<br><br>
Additionally, our experts compare the piece with authentic reference materials, consult databases, and leverage their expertise to assess its overall quality. 
<br><br>
But, if you don’t want to pay the price of authenticating a piece of jewelry, or don’t need a certificate for it, you can always check out one of our guides. There, you’ll find all the details of how to deliver a deliberate authentication.  
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="new-faq_item">
                    <div class="new-faq_item-title">
                        <p class="font-title">
                            Where can I authenticate a ring?
                        </p>
                        <a href="javascript:void(0)" class="font-title">
                            +
                        </a>
                    </div>
                    <div class="new-faq_item-text">
                        <p class="font-description">
                            You can easily authenticate your ring here. 
<br><br>
All you need to do is take some pictures of the ring, and within 12 hours (or even less), you will receive the authentication verdict. Additionally, you will be provided with a certificate confirming the accuracy of the authentication, ensuring that your ring is is indeed a piece of verified jewelry.
<br><br>
While you always have the option to authenticate the ring yourself, we offer a wealth of articles that guide you through the process, providing you with all the necessary details to prove the authenticity of your ring.
<br><br>
However, it is important to note that self-authentication can be risky and potentially dangerous, particularly if you plan to resell the ring. That is why we strongly advise leaving this process to us, the experts.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="new-faq_item">
                    <div class="new-faq_item-title">
                        <p class="font-title">
                           How much does a jewelry authentication service cost?
                        </p>
                        <a href="javascript:void(0)" class="font-title">
                            +
                        </a>
                    </div>
                    <div class="new-faq_item-text">
                        <p class="font-description">
                           The cost of authenticating jewelry typically ranges from $15 to $50, with variations based on factors like the brand and desired turnaround time.
<br><br>
For instance, if you require authentication for a Tiffany & Co ring within 30 minutes, the fee would be $35. However, if you can afford to wait for 12 hours, the cost of authenticating the same ring would be reduced to $15.
<br><br>
In essence, the pricing depends on the timeframe and the brand associated with your jewelry. It's important to consider that the more renowned and exclusive the brand, the higher the authentication cost will be. 
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="new-faq_item">
                    <div class="new-faq_item-title">
                        <p class="font-title">
                            How much does it cost to authenticate a ring?
                        </p>
                        <a href="javascript:void(0)" class="font-title">
                            +
                        </a>
                    </div>
                    <div class="new-faq_item-text">
                        <p class="font-description">
                            The price range for authenticating a ring typically spans from $15 to $105, contingent upon factors like the brand and desired turnaround time.
<br><br>
For instance, if you necessitate authentication for a Tiffany & Co ring within a 30-minute window, the fee would amount to $35. However, if you are able to wait for 12 hours, the cost of authenticating the same ring would be reduced to $15.
<br><br>
Fundamentally, the pricing is contingent upon the timeframe and the brand associated with your ring. It is worth noting that more prestigious and exclusive brands incur higher authentication costs. For instance, the authentication of a Cartier ring would command a significantly higher fee compared to a Tiffany & Co ring.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
            </div>
  <div class="new-faq_bottom font-title">
      <p>Have more questions? Visit our <a href="https://legitgrails.frontkb.com/en">Help Center</a></p>
  </div>
